reviews.review_text: from the honey year Sans discussion of a Dark Star, this show typifies 73 as contrasted with 72. Get this for the Brown Eyed Women which shines in its own sweetness, an incredible Jack Straw, and a unique jam out of Here Comes Sunshine.

The smart choice. Of the two options for this date this has better sound.  Worthwhile even for those not working towards their 73 cert.  I think 5 stars too generous for any part of the show, except perhaps setlist which is outstanding as it is throughout the year.  The sound, mix, and performance rate four stars.  The Eyes and China Doll stand out as really lovely.  Certainly not the most impressive Eyes of the spring tour but competent.  The WBYG is great, off-key and a perfect way to end over three and a half hours of music.

april fools You've got all the classic 73 shows? Try this one. Only less than great because it has some hard competition! The band are in synch and the Wall sounds good tonight. Nice versions of Jack Straw, Loose Lucy, Playin and Half Step. But what really makes this show stand out for me is the rare and only Space Jam out of HC Sunshine. Definitely a fun listen. One to add to your 73 collection.
Dr. Flasback ;-)

Get the other version Like most '73 shows, this one is great. After listening to both sources of it, I found that I like the other one better than this remaster. The instruments and vocals all seem to come through more clear on the original.

Superb show I am a very tough critic of shows, and this one is top-notch. I just finished listening to the entire Spring 73 tour, and this one is without a doubt the best of the bunch. I rank it slightly higher than 3-24 and 3-26. Everyone talks about the HCSS> Jam as they should, but the Eyes is one of the best I've heard, definitely the best of Spring 73, and the China Doll that follows is heart-wrenching.

one of my favorites! Man this show rules. I'd say its in my top 5 favorites at the moment (which change regularly). weather report prelude>eyes is just NUTS and then ends up going into CHINA DOLL!!? followed by sugar mags is just too good to not get you dancing around your living room. check it out if you haven't already!!!
